-- Hydrobudowa Falls as Creditor Files for Its Bankruptcy
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-05-10T09:20:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/hydrobudowa-falls-as-creditor-files-for-its-bankruptcy-correct-.html
(Corrects headline and first paragraph to show that a
creditor filed for Hydrobudowa’s bankruptcy.)  Hydrobudowa Polska SA (HBP) , the unit of
Poland’s third-largest builder PBG SA, lost the most in more
than two weeks in Warsaw after a creditor filed a motion for its
bankruptcy.  The shares declined as much as 9.1 percent, falling the
most since April 23, and traded 5.5 percent lower at 9:15 a.m.
in Warsaw.  The Polish unit of German pipe maker  KSB AG (KSB)  filed for
bankruptcy of Hydrobudowa, the PBG subsidiary said in a
regulatory statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw at 
 pbujnicki@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
